==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dulcamarin
<hw>Dul`ca*ma"rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A glucoside extracted from the bittersweet (<spn>Solanum
Dulcamara</spn>), as a yellow amorphous substance. It probably occasions
the compound taste. See <er>Bittersweet</er>, 3<sd>(a)</sd>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dulce</ent>⟦br⟧
